content.description:
Start up a shallow, left-facing corner through steep, lesser quality rock using the featured rock on the right and the gritty, non-featured rock on the left for a feet. A nice, heavily-chalked block in the corner offers a nice clip hold but doesn't look like it'll be there for long. (I broke two holds in the first 15' of the route in Sept. 2008.)

Pull the crux around the 4th bolt into less steep and easier but run-out climbing past a few more bolts to the bolted anchor.
content.protection: 7 bolts plus a two bolt anchor.
content.location: This climbs up near the center of the west side of Sweet 17.  A shallow left-facing corner to a left-angling crack is easy to spot. This is the route.

content.description: A bit difficult off the ground and then another section at a small bulge in the middle which can be harder or easier depending on whether you go straight up, or move to the right (easier).
content.location: To the right of Monkey Funk

content.description:
As you approach Sweet 17 from the notch in Comp Rock, there are two bolted routes on the south face.  This is the one to the left.

Start up a slab to mantle on big patina buckets.  Granite patina climbing to the chains.
content.location: Head towards the west face of Sweet 17 but stop short of the wall proper.
